<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="217" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1261,1864]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1441,1467]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Remarks:</emphasis>
Re-examination of 
<specimenCount box="[541,711,1441,1468]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">eight paratypes</specimenCount>
from the A. K. Dubey collection (types donated by B. V. David) revealed that the submargin becomes deflexed ventrally in slide-mounted puparia, and the true margin remains hidden below the dorsal surface, the thoracic tracheal furrows are indicated by polygonal markings or faint irregular tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[272,411,1549,1575]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–35" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[158,1430,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 26–35. Editaaleyrodes indicus David, paratypes: 26, puparium; 27, cephalic area; 28, submargin; 29, thoracic tracheal furrow, dorsal side; 30, abdominal segment sutures, pockets; 31, true margin, venter focused; 32, thoracic tracheal furrow, reduced extension in a paratype, dorsal surface; 33, submargin, pores; 34, true margin, ventral setae, venter focused; 35, vasiform orifice, caudal furrow." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5876644" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5876644/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Figs 29, 32</figureCitation>
), the thoracic tracheal folds are not indicated and without polygonal markings and the submargin is folded ventrally (except the narrow caudal pore opening area) (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1203,1585,1611]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–35" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[158,1430,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 26–35. Editaaleyrodes indicus David, paratypes: 26, puparium; 27, cephalic area; 28, submargin; 29, thoracic tracheal furrow, dorsal side; 30, abdominal segment sutures, pockets; 31, true margin, venter focused; 32, thoracic tracheal furrow, reduced extension in a paratype, dorsal surface; 33, submargin, pores; 34, true margin, ventral setae, venter focused; 35, vasiform orifice, caudal furrow." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5876644" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5876644/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Figs 26, 31, 34</figureCitation>
), thus the transverse moulting suture overlaps itself and reaches the lateral margin. These observations contradict those of 
<bibRefCitation author="David, B. V." box="[1286,1436,1621,1648]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" pagination="317 - 320" refId="ref5321" refString="David, B. V. (2005) Editaaleyrodes indicus, a new genus and species of whitefly (Hemiptera: Aleyrodidae), from India. Entomon, 30 (4), 317 - 320." type="journal article" year="2005">David (2005)</bibRefCitation>
and led to a redefinition of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="David" authorityYear="2005" box="[561,729,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Editaaleyrodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[561,729,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Editaaleyrodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which includes details of the vasiform orifice. The examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[227,334,1694,1720]" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">paratypes</typeStatus>
revealed also the following features not mentioned in the original description: thoracic tracheal furrows marked with polygonal markings; thoracic tracheal folds without polygonal markings; caudal furrow with faint tubercles, prominent at caudal pore opening area; submargin folded ventrally; subventral area not demarcated from the submargin (
<figureCitation box="[390,475,1801,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–35" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[158,1430,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 26–35. Editaaleyrodes indicus David, paratypes: 26, puparium; 27, cephalic area; 28, submargin; 29, thoracic tracheal furrow, dorsal side; 30, abdominal segment sutures, pockets; 31, true margin, venter focused; 32, thoracic tracheal furrow, reduced extension in a paratype, dorsal surface; 33, submargin, pores; 34, true margin, ventral setae, venter focused; 35, vasiform orifice, caudal furrow." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5876644" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5876644/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
); first abdominal segment with one pair of geminate pores between setae; abdominal segment sutures and depressions prominent (
<figureCitation box="[653,738,1837,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–41" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1254,1278]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1231]" captionTargetId="figure-31@10.[151,1436,181,1231]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 36–41. Editaaleyrodes indicus David, paratypes: puparium, dorsal surface (36), ventral surface (37–41); 36, vasiform orifice; 37, cephalothoracic area; 38, abdominal area; 39, abdominal segment sutures, pockets; 40, legs, antenna; 41, caudal tracheal fold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5876646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5876646/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
); pockets continuous (
<figureCitation box="[989,1072,1837,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–35" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[158,1430,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 26–35. Editaaleyrodes indicus David, paratypes: 26, puparium; 27, cephalic area; 28, submargin; 29, thoracic tracheal furrow, dorsal side; 30, abdominal segment sutures, pockets; 31, true margin, venter focused; 32, thoracic tracheal furrow, reduced extension in a paratype, dorsal surface; 33, submargin, pores; 34, true margin, ventral setae, venter focused; 35, vasiform orifice, caudal furrow." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5876644" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5876644/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="217">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
